Metasoma . Polished and shining. Tergite II shorter tergite I, with posterior margin evenly convex. Genitalia (
Figs 16–17
) with paramere slightly shorter than basiparamere, very wide, overlapping each other, dorsal half membranous and translucent, apical margin somewhat truncate, dorsal and ventral margins convex in lateral view; digitus wide, progressively narrowing apicad, apex rounded; cuspis slightly longer than digitus; aedeagus diamond-shaped, with pair of rounded apical lobes, apex surpassing cuspis apex and not reaching paramere apex; genital ring with dorsal half projected basad medially.
